\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocals|Best Pop Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocals]]\n|{{won}}<ref name=\"g92\" />\n|-\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Music Video|Best Music Video, Short Form]]\n|{{won}}<ref name=\"g92\" />\n|-\n| \"[[Radio Song]]\"\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Rock Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocal|Best Rock Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocal]]\n|{{nom}}<ref name=\"g92\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Out of Time (album)|Out of Time]]''\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Alternative Music Album|Best Alternative Music Album]]\n|{{won}}<ref name=\"g92\" />\n|-\n| [[Grammy Award for Album of the Year|Album of the Year]]\n|{{nom}}<ref name=\"g92\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[36th Annual Grammy Awards|1994]]\n| \"[[Man on the Moon (song)|Man on the Moon]]\"\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocals|Best Pop Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocals]]\n|{{nom}}<ref name=\"g94\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/awards/37th-annual-grammy-awards |title=37th Annual GRAMMY Awards (1994) |publisher=[[The Recording Academy]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| \"[[Everybody Hurts]]\"\n|  [[Grammy Award for Best Music Video|Best Music Video, Short Form]]\n|{{nom}}<ref name=\"g94\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Automatic for the People]]''\n| [[Grammy Award for Best Alternative Music Album|Best Alternative Music Album]]\n|{{nom}}<ref name=\"g94\" />\n|-\n| [[Grammy Award for Album of the Year|Album of the Year]]\n|{{nom}}<ref name=\"g94\" />\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[37th Annual Grammy Awards|1995]]\n| ''[[Monster (R.E.M. album)|Monster]]''\n|  [[Grammy Award for Best Rock Album|Best Rock Album]]\n|{{nom}}<ref name=\"g95\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/awards/38th-annual-grammy-awards |title=38th Annual GRAMMY Awards (1995) |publisher=[[The Recording Academy]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[39th Annual Grammy Awards|1997]]\n| ''[[New Adventures in Hi-Fi]]''\n|  [[Grammy Award for Best Alternative Music Album|Best Alternative Music Album]]\n|{{nom}}<ref name=\"g97\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/awards/40th-annual-grammy-awards |title=40th Annual GRAMMY Awards (1997) |publisher=[[The Recording Academy]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[44th Annual Grammy Awards|2001]]\n| \"[[The Great Beyond]]\"\n|  [[Grammy Award for Best Song Written for Visual Media|Best Song Written for a Motion Picture, Television or Other Visual Media]]\n|{{nom}}<ref name=\"g01\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/awards/38th-annual-grammy-awards |title=44th Annual GRAMMY Awards (2001) |publisher=[[The Recording Academy]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[45th Annual Grammy Awards|2002]]\n| \"[[Imitation of Life (song)|Imitation of Life]]\"\n|  [[Grammy Award for Best Pop Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocals|Best Pop Performance by a Duo or Group with Vocals]]\n|{{nom}}<ref name=\"g02\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/awards/38th-annual-grammy-awards |title=45th Annual GRAMMY Awards (2002) |publisher=[[The Recording Academy]]}}</ref>\n{{end}}\n\n'''MTV Europe Music Awards'''\n\n{{award table}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[1995 MTV Europe Music Awards|1995]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| R.E.M.\n| Best Live Act\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[2001 MTV Europe Music Awards|2001]]\n| Best Group\n|{{nom}}\n{{end}}\n\n'''MTV Video Music Awards'''\n\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[1988 MTV Video Music Awards|1988]]\n| \"[[The One I Love (R.E.M. song)|The One I Love]]\"\n| Best Direction\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| [[1989 MTV Video Music Awards|1989]]\n| \"[[Orange Crush (song)|Orange Crush]]\"\n| Best Post-Modern Video\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"9\"| [[1991 MTV Video Music Awards|1991]]\n| rowspan=\"8\"| \"[[Losing My Religion]]\"\n| Video of the Year\n|{{won}}\n|-\n| Best Group Video\n|{{won}}\n|-\n| Breakthrough Video\n|{{won}}\n|-\n| Best Direction\n|{{won}}\n|-\n| Best A