i+term#v=onepage&q=jogi%20term&f=false | title=Maharashtra| isbn=9788179911020| last1=Singh| first1=Kumar Suresh| last2=Bhanu| first2=B. V.| last3=India| first3=Anthropological Survey of| year=2004}}</ref> It is a colloquial term for the word [[Yogi]] that refers to the people who practised [[Yoga]] as part of their daily rituals. Over time, this led to the formation of this community and subsequent castes.\n\n==History==\nThe ''Jogis'' were weaver and inhabited the al parts of [[India]]. They are [[Hindus|Hindu]] by religion and have been claimed to have sacred thread on their body. But they are regarded as very inferior [[Shudra]] by [[Caste system in India]]. They have been claimed to be descendants of the mendicants of [[Gorakhpur]] called Jogi as [[Sannyasa|Sanyasi]] and [[Vairagi]].{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n\n==Classification==\nMost of the Indian states have listed the Jogi caste in the [[Other Backward Classes]] since 1993.\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:98%\"\n! | '''Officially recognized names'''\n! |'''Regions with OBC status'''\n! | '''Designation'''\n! class=\"unsortable\" | '''Notes'''\n|-\n|Jogi\n| [[Andhra Pradesh]]<ref name=\"Andhra Pradesh \" /><sup>10</sup>\n| 12011/68/93-BCC (C ) 10 September 1993\n|\n|-\n|Yogi,\nJogi,\nJugi Nath\n| [[Assam]]<ref name=\"Assam\" /><sup>26</sup>\n| 12011/68/93-BCC(C) 10/09/1993\n|\n|-\n|Jogi (Jugi)\n| [[Bihar]]<ref name=\"Bihar\" /><sup>44</sup>\n| 12011/68/93-BCC(C) 10 September 1993\n|\n|-\n|Jogi, Nath\n| [[Chandigarh]]<ref name=\"Chandigarh\" /><sup>30</sup>\n| 12011/99/94-BCC 11 December 1997\n|\n|-\n|Garpagari\nJoginath, Nathjogi\n| [[Chhattisgarh]]<ref name=\"Chhattisgarh\" /><sup>22</sup>\n| 12015/2/2007-BCC 18 August 2010\n|\n|-\n|Nath,\nJogi\n| [[Daman and Diu]]<ref name=\"Daman and Diu\" /><sup>16</sup>\n| 12011/9/94-BCC 19 October 1994\n|\n|-\n|Jogi,\n| [[Delhi]]<ref name=\"Delhi\" /><sup>25</sup>\n| 12011/7/95-BCC 24 May 1995\n|\n|-\n|Nathjogi\n| [[Goa]]<ref name=\"Goa\" /><sup>7</sup>\n| 1